    "answer_id" : 32154951,
    "question_id" : 8608710,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>Simple &amp; short solution worked for me.</p>\n\n<p>Go to <code>File</code> -> <code>Settings</code> -> <code>Editor</code> -> <code>Auto Import</code> -> <code>Java</code> (left panel) and make the below things:\nSelect check box for  \"<code>Add unambigious imports on the fly</code>\" and \"<code>Optimize imports on the fly</code>\"</p>\n\n<p>Refer this.</p>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://i.sstatic.net/hZBUB.png\"><img src=\"https://i.sstatic.net/hZBUB.png\" alt=\"enter image description here\"></a></p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 379556,
      "reputation" : 1031,
      "user_id" : 733002,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 93,
      "profile_image" : "https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/0ac72d5aed0bdbc13403c0d42c3646b5?s=256&d=identicon&r=PG",
      "display_name" : "Joe",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/733002/joe"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 9,
    "last_activity_date" : 1441784308,
    "creation_date" : 1441784308,
    "answer_id" : 32473613,
    "question_id" : 8608710,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>In IntelliJ 14, the path to the settings for Auto Import has changed. The path is </p>\n\n<p>IntelliJ IDEA->Preferences->Editor->General->Auto Import</p>\n\n<p>then follow the instructions above, clicking \n  Add unambiguous imports on the fly</p>\n\n<p>I can't imagine why this wouldn't be set by default.</p>\n"
  }, {
    "owner" : {
      "account_id" : 158578,
      "reputation" : 3221,
      "user_id" : 377320,
      "user_type" : "registered",
      "accept_rate" : 25,
      "profile_image" : "https://i.sstatic.net/XEy0o.jpg?s=256",
      "display_name" : "Martin Vysny",
      "link" : "https://stackoverflow.com/users/377320/martin-vysny"
    },
    "is_accepted" : false,
    "score" : 2,
    "last_activity_date" : 1470812024,
    "creation_date" : 1470812024,
    "answer_id" : 38866236,
    "question_id" : 8608710,
    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>I finally created a workaround around this frustrating issue. I'm not completely happy with the workaround, but it's better than nothing. </p>\n\n<p>Basically, after you paste the source code and unambigous imports are fixed, just press <code>F2</code> to highlight the next compiler error. If the current error is an import-missing error, press <code>Alt+Enter</code>, then <code>Enter</code> to select the <code>Import</code> option, then pick the correct import. Then, press <code>F2</code> again.</p>\n"
  }, {
